About

In conclusion, this study aims to bridge the gap in literature by employing an extensive analysis of World Bank demographic data to explore the interconnections between GDP, birth rates, and womens political participation in Pakistan, India, and Bangladesh. Through exploratory data analysis and innovative visualizations, the research intends to provide policymakers, public health officials, NGOs, and the academic community with actionable insights to refine and enhance family planning initiatives, considering the unique demographic and cultural contexts of South Asia.
